node.text: Me time

ɴᴀᴛʜᴀɴ, 40, ᴀᴜsᴛɪɴ, ᴛᴇxᴀs—I normally wear boxer trunks. I like that they don’t show above the belt. On weekends I live in Levi’s 501s, and nothing beats a crisp new pair of y-briefs. That’s old-school class. You can’t change that.
Pierre wears Y-Briefs in Burgundy for Valentine’s Day.

ᴘᴀᴛʀɪᴄᴋ, 27, ᴀᴍᴇʀɪᴄᴀɴ ɢᴀʀᴅᴇɴs ʙᴜɪʟᴅɪɴɢ, ᴜᴘᴘᴇʀ ᴇᴀsᴛ sɪᴅᴇ, ɴʏᴄ—I believe in taking care of myself, a balanced diet and a rigorous exercise routine. Each morning, I put on a pair of boxer trunks to do my stomach crunches. I can do a thousand now.

sᴛᴇᴘʜᴀɴ, 41, ɢʀᴇᴇɴᴡɪᴄʜ ᴠɪʟʟᴀɢᴇ, ɴᴇᴡ ʏᴏʀᴋ—The new year for me is a clean slate—a fresh start. I’m sticking to tonic water tonight; I’m not trying to take on 2020 with bags under my eyes. While New York City nurses its collective hangover tomorrow morning, I’ll be bright-eyed and bushy-tailed, ready to embrace the new decade with a pair of Sea Island Boxer Shorts I’ve been saving for a special occasion.
